column1: These are the results from the latest WABDL Bench Press and Dead Lift Championships:
PLEASE NOTIFY GUS RETHWISCH on his cell (503) 901-1622 OF ANY OVERSIGHTS OR MISSPELLING OF NAMES.
Results are posted as soon as they are received in the WABDL office and verified.
IF THE WABDL OFFICE DOES NOT DO THE MEET PREPARATION, ONLY THE RECORDS FROM THE MEET WILL BE POSTED ON THE WEBSITE!
Rancho Cordova, CA - July 8           Bench Press       Dead Lift

Occasionally, meet directors do not adhere to the weight limits for a particular weight class. This is most likely an oversight. However, when that happens, there is an adjustment made placing the lifter in the correct weight class for the meet results. For the lifters' information, the following weight class limits are listed. If a lifter's weight class is changed from a meet, (s)he needs to consult this chart to see if the weight class limit had been exceeded or if body weight was insufficient for the weight class. Also, according to WABDL rules, if a lifter is given a fourth attempt and was not entitled to it (not within 16 kilos or 35.2 pounds of a record or did not make second or third lift), the fourth lift does not count in the meet results.
